14 May 2012 17:53






Pauli's got the general idea. This thing has an unknown, non-biological contagion associated with anything that emerges, and if you give that contagion's carrier a plane, that's bad. Also, this object can't be moved, and its containment procedures necessitate its own armed containment site with over 1,000 personnel devoted solely to it. That's a pretty involved and complex containment procedure, even if it does boil down to .

One more thing, there are ships that have emerged that don't correspond to any recorded ship lost from crossing SCP-1372. That means there's a possibility that there are ships that weren't built on Earth emerging from it.

I actually did waffle a lot between Euclid and Keter on this, but eventually decided to err on the side of  on the grounds that there are aspects of this thing that are totally unknown, it has the potential for serious damage if it does slip past ACS-70 somehow, and it requires a very involved method of containment.







